---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const pageTitle = "About Me";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-body">
          <h1 class="title">About Me</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">Hi, I'm Roger Rajaratnam aka Sourcier</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="section">
        <div class="content">
          <section id="about">
            <p>
              I'm a software engineer and technical lead based in London,
              passionate about building things on the web and solving problems
              through technology. My journey into software engineering started
              with a curiosity about how digital products work behind the scenes
              — that curiosity eventually turned into a career focused on
              designing and building scalable applications.
            </p>

            <p>
              Over the years, I've worked across a range of projects in fintech
              and consumer technology, primarily as a full-stack engineer. I
              enjoy working across the entire stack, from crafting intuitive
              front-end experiences to designing backend systems that are
              reliable, scalable, and maintainable. Much of my work today sits
              at the intersection of engineering, architecture, and leadership —
              helping teams build high-quality software while also thinking
              about the bigger technical picture.
            </p>

            <p>
              One of the most rewarding aspects of my career has been helping
              other developers grow. I've spent time mentoring engineers and
              teaching at coding bootcamps, supporting people as they transition
              into software engineering and develop their skills. Watching
              someone go from writing their first lines of code to confidently
              building applications is incredibly fulfilling.
            </p>

            <p>
              I studied Computer Software Engineering at the University of
              Westminster, which gave me the foundations that shaped my path
              into full-stack development. Since then, I've had the opportunity
              to work with different teams, technologies, and products — each
              experience teaching me something new about building software and
              collaborating with others.
            </p>

            <p>
              This blog is a place where I share ideas, lessons learned, and
              practical insights from my experience in software engineering.
              Sometimes that might mean writing about system design, web
              development, or technical leadership. Other times it might simply
              be reflections on things I've learned along the way.
            </p>

            <p>
              Outside of work, I'm always exploring new technologies, thinking
              about better ways to build software, and staying curious about how
              the web continues to evolve.
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
